 and gaps with the\nexact results for the infinite lattice drawn from the Bethe-Ansatz solution.\nThe deviations are boundary-condition dependent. The special torsion yields\nmore rapid convergence than open or periodic boundary conditions. For sizes as\nsmall as $L=7$, the numerical results for twisted condition are very close to\nthe $L\\to\\infty$ limit. We also discuss the ground-state electronic density and\nmagnetization at half filling under the three boundary conditions.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Tue, 20 Jun 2017 17:57:57 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Fri, 7 Jul 2017 17:58:41 GMT"}],"update_date":"2017-07-10"}
